    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="746"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.4016/59: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="9" xml:id="d746fn9">Forwarded by the Commission to Negotiate Peace as
                        No. 2381.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-30T23:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 30, 1919, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 1, 1.12 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Department’s 17, May 28, 6 p.m., received this evening.</p>
                <p>Since my arrival in Poland I have endeavored to inform myself fully as to the
                    treatment of Jews but possess no evidence which <pb facs="0837" n="752"
                        xml:id="pg_752"/> would warrant charges referred to in Department’s telegram
                    or afford me any data to start specific investigations, therefore I should be
                    glad to have Department furnish me a definite list of places where these events
                    occurred, a statement of the charges made, the events in each place and if
                    possible names of victims and of possible witnesses. If Department approves, I
                    am then prepared to ask Doctor Bogen, director of the Jewish Joint Distribution
                    Committee for Poland, and Lieutenant Colonel Bailey of the Red Cross to
                    accompany me and make careful personal investigation in the various places. See
                    my number 35.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
